article.headline: Lafayette 68, Lehigh 66
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- Andrew Brown scored 26 points as Lafayette held off rival Lehigh for a 68-66 victory on Sunday. Brown's points came on 10-of-16 shooting for Lafayette (8-19, 4-8 Patriot League), which knocked away an in-bounds pass as time expired to clinch the win over Lehigh (15-11, 5-7). Jared Mintz added 21 points for Lafayette, Ryan Willen scored 8 and Michael Gruner had 6. Zahir Carrington led Lehigh with 15 points, while Marquis Hall added 12 and Prentice Small, Dave Buchberger and Phil Anderson each scored ten.
